                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/90: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-23T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>560. Your 685, December 16, 6 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department informed that Captain F. B. Upham, Naval Attaché your Embassy, has
                    been designated by Navy Department as its representative in all matters dealing
                    with the construction of this airship. The conditions and specifications
                    required by the Navy Department are being sent him direct. You are requested if
                    necessary to support him in the conduct of his negotiations and to notify the
                    Conference of Ambassadors of his designation. Inform Berlin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
